{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"679c5a8d-d8c7-4c8d-8a1a-b425039dafee","content":"Here's what you need to do:\n\n1. **Remove** the `xunit.runner.visualstudio` package reference.\n\n2. **Add** the `xunit.runner.mtp` package (matches your xUnit version):\n   ```xml\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.mtp\" Version=\"2.9.3\" />\n   ```\n\n3. **Enable MTP** in your project file:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n4. **Run tests** the same way:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n\nThe `TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport` property ensures `dotnet test` uses MTP instead of VSTest. Without it, you'd need to run the test executable directly.\n\nThat's it — no code changes needed in your tests themselves.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e7254880-bf15-4163-a1a0-7c8635c808eb","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using `xunit.runner.visualstudio`) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP). Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of this migration.","outputTokens":295},"id":"291ee01b-e6ba-4d9c-a9c8-e2763b7e0873","timestamp":"2026-04-07T15:54:14.884Z","parentId":"0f097091-6a0c-48af-bb7f-3f5dea9cd1b0"}
